# Epic 2: Admin Dashboard - Core Administration & Multi-User Setup

## Problem Analysis

- **Goal**: Provide administrators with tools to manage application settings (branding), control user registration, create and manage other user accounts, and enable all users to manage their profiles.
- **Key Requirements**:
  - Create admin dashboard layout and navigation
  - Implement user profile management
  - Build admin user management interface
  - Create application branding management
  - Implement user registration control setting

## Current Status

### 2025-05-27 07:18

**Status**: Planned

- What's working: N/A - Planning phase
- What's not: N/A - Not started implementation
- Blocking issues: Epic 1 needs to be completed first
- Next actions: Complete Epic 1, then begin with Story 2.1
- Documentation updates needed:
  - [ ] Admin dashboard structure documentation
  - [ ] User management flows
  - [ ] Branding configuration guide

## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 2.1: Create Basic Admin Dashboard Layout and Navigation**
  - [ ] Create admin route protection logic
  - [ ] Implement admin layout component
  - [ ] Build persistent left sidebar navigation
  - [ ] Add ordered navigation links for all admin functions
  - [ ] Create admin landing page
  - Success criteria: Admin dashboard with secure routes and consistent navigation
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (Authentication, Middleware)

- [ ] **Story 2.2: Implement User Profile Management (Self-Service)**
  - [ ] Create dedicated profile page
  - [ ] Add read-only user name display
  - [ ] Implement password change section
  - [ ] Create avatar management section (upload, preview, remove)
  - [ ] Build backend APIs for profile operations
  - Success criteria: Users can manage their profiles (password, avatar)
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 2.3: Implement Admin User Management**
  - [ ] Create user management page
  - [ ] Build user list display with all required columns
  - [ ] Implement "Create New User" functionality
  - [ ] Add "Edit User" capability
  - [ ] Create backend APIs for user management
  - Success criteria: Admins can list, create, and edit users (name, role, status)
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1, Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [ ] **Story 2.4: Implement Application Branding Management**
  - [ ] Create branding management page
  - [ ] Add application name customization
  - [ ] Implement logo image upload
  - [ ] Add favicon image upload
  - [ ] Build backend APIs for branding management
  - Success criteria: Admins can customize app name, logo, and favicon
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1

- [ ] **Story 2.5: Implement User Registration Control Setting**
  - [ ] Add section to admin settings page
  - [ ] Create UI for toggling user creation permission
  - [ ] Implement persistence mechanism
  - [ ] Update user creation UI based on setting
  - [ ] Build backend API for settings management
  - Success criteria: Admins can enable/disable user creation with confirmation
  - Dependencies: Story 2.1, Story 2.3

## Affected Components

- Admin dashboard layout and navigation
- User profile management UI
- Admin user management UI
- Application branding configuration
- System settings management
- Backend APIs for all admin functions

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (Authentication, User Schema, Middleware)
- Material UI v6
- File upload handling (formidable)
- Image processing

## Technical Considerations

- Admin routes require strict access control
- File uploads need proper validation and security
- Avatar and branding images require proper storage strategy
- User management must include safeguards (can't remove last admin)
- Settings must be properly persisted and retrieved

